# AI-Based LBW Review System (Mini Project)

## 📌 Project Overview
This project demonstrates an **AI-assisted Leg Before Wicket (LBW) review system** using computer vision and simple trajectory modeling.

The system is designed for **academic demonstration** and follows the **actual LBW decision logic used in cricket**, focusing on clarity and explainability rather than full professional accuracy.

---

## 🏏 LBW Decision Logic (Cricket Rules)
An LBW decision depends on answering **two key questions**:

1. **Impact Line Check (Front View)**  
   Did the ball hit the batsman **in line with the stumps**?

2. **Wicket Collision Check (Side View)**  
   Would the ball have **hit the stumps** if the pad was not there?

👉 If **both conditions are satisfied**, the batsman is given **OUT**.

---

## 🧠 System Approach
- Uses a **front-view video** of a cricket delivery
- Tracks the ball using classical computer vision
- Simulates a **side-view trajectory** (when side-view video is unavailable)
- Visualizes the decision using **two simplified cricket-style diagrams**

This approach is **honest, explainable, and suitable for a 6th Semester Mini Project**.

---

## 📊 Visualizations Used
### 1️⃣ Front View – Impact Line
- Shows the **stump line**
- Marks the **exact impact point**
- Clearly indicates **INLINE / OUTSIDE LINE**

### 2️⃣ Side View – Trajectory to Stumps
- Shows the **pitch**
- Shows **three stumps**
- Predicts whether the ball would **hit or miss the stumps**

All visuals use **consistent colors and cricket terminology**.

